         I see nothing wrong with what he did. That kind of excitement(whether I'm on the giving or recieving end) is what makes me drop by SZ from time to time to play. Most of my friends play on druzzil and it will always be my main server, but the appeal of SZ is too much to avoid. :)</P><P>SZ is a "no rules" PvP server. it was designed for the adrenaline junkies/hardcore PvPers to roam and get their jollies off. The fact that Fancy does this *AND* roleplays (for the most part) at the same time is what I find really nice about it. (I still can't belive 2 people answered the a/s/l. ) He knows he's getting a bad rep with newts and evils, but he doesn't care. They are considered the enemy and if that's how he chooses to play his character on a no rules server then so be it. If I had been one of those newts, I would have laughed it off and gone elsewhere or logged on druzzil for awhile until he left. They chose to stay. Happens once, shame on you. Happens twice, shame on me. Happens a third time and I'm a moron that deserves it.</P><P>I find it sad that the GMs actually stepped in..the players could have stopped it themselves if they really wanted to. that is the point of a PVP server is it not? (as was mentioned, perhaps to stop the slaughter due to corpse/lag reasons, but thats the only reason i could see for GM intervention) If the GMs don't like the ability he used then they should just make POD non agro unless directly attacked for that server.</P><P>If you want rules on a PvP server then go to vallon,rallos, or tallon zek. Pick the one that suits your style. Going to SZ and expecting GM inervention is like going to a RP server and telling the roleplayers to stop roleplaying. Your trying to make the server into something it wasn't designed for.</P><P>just my 2cp </P><P>~Bonez</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
